      %h2 Your big boots styling

      %h3
        Which colour is right for you and how to style big boots
      
      %p
        Picking the right colour is going to be the make or break of your autumn/winter wardrobe and your big boot purchase.

      %ul
        %li
          Pick a colour carefully – for example you need to know how to wear white boots with your wardrobe if you choose them
        %li
          If you like wearing all black, think about a contrasting or neutral colour for your boots, that will complement a full black outfit
        %li
          Most colours go well with all black outfits, so you are free to be as adventurous as you want when choosing a contrasting colour for your boots
        %li
          Big black boots also work well if your wardrobe is full of colours, or neutral shades
        %li
          If you are unsure, try a few different colours on with your most worn outfit and see how you feel and look in them

      %h3 
        What price is right for you

      %p
        Budgets vary and so does quality.
        If you plan to wear your big boots all the time it is best to go for a good strong sole that won’t wear out too quickly, especially if you want it to last a few seasons.

      %p
        Here are some more tips to help you balance price with quality:

      %ul
        %li
          The main part of the boot should also be made of a good quality material, one that you are happy with and that will last throughout winter weather
        %li
          Additional material is also important.
          Whether it has elasticated sides or otherwise, do make sure the additional material will withstand the level of use you have planned and the weather you expect to wear them out in
        %li
          Comfort and ease of use is always another great thing to consider. 
          If it is cold and wet outside you don’t want to come in and be struggling with a big wet boot and cold hands either

      %p
        Choose wisely and remember if you make the right choice now and you, your boots, and your wardrobe will have a great few seasons together. 

